4. Finds the position of the null terminator using `find_first_of(0)`
5. Gets a string view of the message up to (but not including) the null terminator
6. Advances the read pointer past the null terminator
7. Returns the populated `MessagePacket` structure

The code follows the patterns shown in the provided examples, particularly the string view deserialization approach demonstrated in the code fragments.

